{
  "texts": [
    "Schwarz et al. (2020) employed ML techniques to explore the cis-regulatory code governing the response to iron deficiency in Arabidopsis roots.",
    "In the realm of plant disease resistance, SVM and its variants are widely employed, as demonstrated by Pal et al. (2016), achieving high accuracy in predicting disease resistance proteins.",
    "ML has also been instrumental in predicting pathogen effector proteins, with Sperschneider et al. (2016) developing EFFECTORP, the first ML classifier for fungal effectors.",
    "Despite the focus on disease resistance genes, ML algorithms hold promise in understanding genes susceptible to plant diseases, contributing significantly to agricultural practices (Yang and Guo, 2017).",
    "The application of ML in exploring plant single-cell genomic data offers opportunities to unravel cellular heterogeneity, decode regulatory networks, and identify novel cell types."
  ]
}